summary: [NO SPOILERS]Whose performance do you think has improved the most over the course of the show?
title: [NO SPOILERS]Whose performance do you think has improved the most over the course of the show?
body:
There were plenty of people who started out great, and didn’t need to improve. There were others that started off pretty poorly, but got better. I think that Emilia Clarke definitely has a top spot here. She’s not incredible by any stretch of the imagination, but I think that she has improved a lot since the beginning of the show. I also think that Nikolaj Coster-Waldau’s accent has improved a lot as well. His accent was never terrible, but in the beginning of the show I don’t think he hides his Denmark accent too well. As the show goes on though, he improves a lot at hiding it. Who are your biggest picks for people that have improved? Even if they weren’t on the show for too long.



Source: https://ift.tt/2K92KqR

title: We didn’t start the Fandoms
body:
So, my bestie and I came up with these alternative lyrics to “We didn’t start the fire” by Billy Joel and they were such fun to make, so I decided to publish them and see, what happens :D

Here we go: 

Sherlock Holmes solves mysteries,
Jon Snow will not bend the knee,
Weeping Angels come for you -
where the hell is Doctor Who?

Loki has an evil plan,
fly away with Iron Man,
the Upside-Down will never rest,
what happend in Budapest

Mother Russia worth her Money,
Bluebell the mutated Bunny,
Lannisters who pay their dept,
Cersei just blew up the sept

we didn’t start the fandoms!
They were all compelling
since the book’s been selling
we didn’t start the fandoms!
but we wrote the fiction
with our best of diction

Doomsday,
Sherlock dying,
Mofftis has all of us crying,
Odin only loved Thor,
not the droids you’re looking for

Deadpool steals your unicorn
using it for privat porn,
Harry defeats you know who,
where did Luna put her shoe

Sam and Dean drive through the night,
Your father’s on the dark side,
Hulk is angry at all times,
Smaug is sleeping on these dimes

we didn’t start the fandoms!
They were all compelling
since the book’s been selling
we didn’t start the fandoms!
but we wrote the fiction
with our best of diction

blog.title: sansa stark & sandor clegane are soulmates

summary: Season 8 SanSan Checklist Posted June 2018, based on Tyrion & Shae’s conversation in “Baelor,” which I believe to be a statement...
body:
Season 8 SanSan Checklist

Posted June 2018, based on Tyrion & Shae’s conversation in “Baelor,” which I believe to be a statement of principles by GRRM and D&D about what a quality Westerosi marriage might include (plus love and babies, of course). 

Specifically, I think this conversation is a sassier, more pragmatic substitute for Sansa and Sandor’s exchange in the books about “what does he want?” (“pretty words your septa taught you, smell good, be his lady love” etc etc.) and I believe it does allude to them in particular, as the great love of the story.

I have a strong suspicion that we will see almost of these “demands” executed in Sansa x Sandor scenes in season eight; I believe it is, indeed, a relationship checklist posted very early in the story so that the writers look like structural geniuses when they pay it off seven years later.

HIS LIST

☐ Companionship: I want you to share my tent 

☐ Caretaking: I want you to pour my wine 

☐ Joy: I want you to laugh at my jokes 

☐ Kindness: I want you to rub my legs when they’re sore after a long day’s ride*

☐ Fidelity: I want you to take no other man to bed for as long as we’re together 

☐ Unity: I want you to fuck me like it’s my last night in this world–which it may well be (two halves of a greater whole; one flesh)

HER LIST

☐ Safety: No one will hurt you for as long as you’re mine (”you may now cloak the bride and bring her under your protection,” “I’ll keep you safe,” successful alpha males protect their mates and offspring from predation and marauding lone males)

☐ Happiness: The pleasure of my company, which I’ve heard is spectacular (orgasms and flirtation, charming witty conversation)

☐ Abundance: More gold than you could spend if you lived a thousand years (note that the thousand years figure comes up often in discussions of legacies and dynasties; you would never guess at this point in the story that Sandor might have Lannister-level money, but…since they spent all theirs, he might have collected more of it than you’d think along the way; handy for rebuilding castles and feeding hungry smallfolk after a devastating war)

**note: TYRION DOES NOT RIDE HORSES ALMOST EVER “he prefers litters,” says Pod at one point; the Hound is very closely associated with horses, because…knight
